🔍 Insights

1998 is the strongest “golden year”
  * High critic score (9.32)
  * High user score (9.40)
  * Very small disagreement → strong consensus

1997 shows a major gap
  * Users loved games far more than critics

2008–2010 era
  * Users consistently rated games higher than critics
  * Suggests rise of **player-driven experiences (online/multiplayer)**

🎯 Final Conclusion

🥇 The Golden Era: Late 1990s (Especially 1998)
* Highest critic scores
* Strong agreement between critics and users
* Release of many iconic and influential games

📈 Key Trends

*Nintendo’s dominance shaped early gaming success
*Shift from offline classics → online multiplayer experiences
*Increasing number of releases over time, but quality consistency slightly drops

🚀 Key Takeaways

* The true golden era is not just about sales, but critical acclaim + player satisfaction
* 1998 stands out as the peak year in gaming history
* Modern gaming excels in scale, but older eras excel in impact and innovation
